Subject:
Availability of an interdisciplinary course MM 5010 ADVANCED
 ENGINEERING MATERIALS in JULY-NOV. 2016 in F SLOT

Body:
b"      Dear Students:     Sub: Availability of an Interdisciplinary Elective: MM 5010 Advanced Engg. Materials Offered in F Slot  reg.    This is to bring to your attention that an interdisciplinary elective entitled MM 5010 Advanced Engineering Materials is available in F Slot this JulyNov. 2016 Semester for registration. It will serve the interests of students from across the departments. The syllabus is given below. Do register for the course if you deem the course useful in your research/career.   With regards,   V.SAMPATH      Title: MM 5010 Advanced Engineering Materials    Objective : This course provides a strong foundation to aid comprehension in contemporary trends in advanced engineering materials. At the end of this course, the student will understand basic principles in the discipline and will be able relate them to materials engineering practice.  Contents : Material selection principles, Advances in ferrous and nonferrous alloys, Intermetallics, Ceramics, Composites, Energy materials (fuel cells, batteries, energy storage systems, etc.), Biomaterials, Magnetic materials, Superconductors, Nanomaterialssynthesis and processing, lightemitting materials, lowdimensional materials (principles, processing and applications).  Text Books : 1. William F. Smith: Principles of Materials Science and Engineering, McGrawHill,  First Indian Edition, New Delhi, 1996. 2. M. R. Srinivasan: Applied Solid State Physics: A Textbook of Materials Science,  ;  New Age International Publishers, First Edition, Delhi, 2012.  References:  A. R. West: Solid State Chemistry and its Applications, John Wiley and Sons, Wiley Student's Second Edition, Singapore, 2005. ASM Handbook: Vols. 1 and 2, ASM International, First Edition, Ohio, USA, 1990. B. Viswanathan: An Introduction to Energy Sources (Ebook), First Edition, IITMadras, Chennai, 2006.  Mark Ratner and Daniel Ratner: Nanotechnology, Pearson Education, First Edition, Delhi, 2003.   Dr.V.Sampath   Professor Department of Metallurgical and Materials Engineering Indian Institute of Technology Madras Chennai  600036 India Phone: 0091442257 (Off.)/2257 6773(Res.) FAX: 009144225705 / 22570509"

